        <p class="info-page__eyebrow">We've Got Answers</p>
        <h1 class="info-page__hero-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p class="info-page__hero-sub">Everything you need to know about buying beds and mattresses online in the UK from Klawford.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container info-page__body">
      <div class="faq-nav">
        <button class="faq-nav__btn active" data-cat="delivery">Delivery</button>
        <button class="faq-nav__btn" data-cat="returns">Returns &amp; Trial</button>
        <button class="faq-nav__btn" data-cat="products">Products &amp; Sizes</button>
        <button class="faq-nav__btn" data-cat="payment">Finance &amp; Payment</button>
        <button class="faq-nav__btn" data-cat="warranty">Warranty</button>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-group" data-cat="delivery">
          <h2 class="faq-group__title">Delivery Questions</h2>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">How long does delivery take for beds and mattresses in the UK?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>All Klawford orders to UK mainland addresses are delivered within <strong>7–14 working days</strong> from the date your order is placed. Because our beds and mattresses are handmade to order, this gives our team time to build your piece to the highest standard. You'll receive an email with your tracking details as soon as your order is dispatched.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Is delivery really free on all Klawford orders?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Yes — standard delivery to UK mainland addresses is completely free on every Klawford order, with no minimum spend required. For deliveries to Scottish Highlands, Northern Ireland, or the Republic of Ireland, a surcharge may apply. Please contact us at <strong>sales@clickclickstore.co.uk</strong> for a quote to your postcode before ordering.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Do you offer weekend or next-day bed delivery?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>We offer weekend delivery slots in select UK postcodes, subject to availability. Next-day delivery is not currently available as our beds are made to order. If a specific delivery date is important to you, please contact our team before placing your order and we'll do our best to accommodate your requirements.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What happens if I'm not home when my bed is delivered?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Our delivery carrier will leave a calling card with instructions to rearrange. We'll also attempt to call the phone number on your order before delivery. We recommend providing a mobile number so we can send you an SMS the morning of delivery with your 2-hour arrival window.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What is your White Glove delivery service?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Our White Glove delivery service upgrades your standard delivery to a full room-of-choice service. A two-person specialist team will carry your bed or mattress to the room you specify, complete full assembly of your bed frame, and remove all packaging from your home. Old bed and mattress disposal is available as an additional add-on. Select White Glove at checkout.</p></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-group" data-cat="returns" style="display:none">
          <h2 class="faq-group__title">Returns &amp; Sleep Trial</h2>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What is Klawford's mattress return policy?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>All Klawford mattresses come with a <strong>60-night risk-free sleep trial</strong>. If you are not completely satisfied with your mattress within 60 nights of delivery, contact our team and we will arrange a free collection from your home and refund you in full — no questions asked, no restocking fees, no hassle.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">How long does it take to get a refund after returning a mattress?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Once your mattress has been collected, we initiate your refund within 1–2 working days. The refund will appear in your account within <strong>3–5 working days</strong> for credit and debit cards, or 1–3 working days for PayPal and digital wallets. Finance refunds are processed through your finance provider.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Do I need to keep the original mattress packaging to return it?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>No — you do not need the original packaging to return a mattress under our 60-night trial. Our collection team will take the mattress as-is. For bed frame returns, however, the original packaging must be retained as items should be returned unused.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Why do I need to sleep on the mattress for at least 14 nights?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Your body naturally takes time to adapt to a new sleep surface, especially if you are switching from a different firmness level or mattress type. We ask for a minimum of 14 nights so your body has a genuine chance to adjust and you can make a fully informed decision. After that point, if you're still not satisfied, we'll collect it for free.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Can I return a bed frame?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Yes — bed frames can be returned within 14 days of delivery provided they are unused and in their original packaging. Please contact us at <strong>sales@clickclickstore.co.uk</strong> to arrange. Bespoke or custom-made frames cannot be returned unless they arrive faulty or damaged.</p></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-group" data-cat="products" style="display:none">
          <h2 class="faq-group__title">Products &amp; Sizes</h2>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What bed sizes do Klawford offer?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Klawford beds are available in all standard UK sizes: <strong>Small Single (2'6" / 75cm), Single (3' / 90cm), Small Double (4' / 120cm), Double (4'6" / 135cm), King (5' / 150cm), and Super King (6' / 180cm)</strong>. Available sizes vary by product — please check each product listing for specific options.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Are Klawford beds and mattresses handmade in the UK?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Yes — every Klawford bed frame and mattress is <strong>handcrafted to order in the United Kingdom</strong> by our team of skilled artisans. We do not import mass-produced products. Each piece is built specifically for the customer who ordered it, using premium UK-sourced materials and subject to strict quality checks before dispatch.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What is the difference between a pocket sprung and memory foam mattress?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>A <strong>pocket sprung mattress</strong> uses individually wrapped steel coils that move independently, providing responsive support and excellent airflow — great for those who sleep hot or prefer a traditional, bouncy feel. A <strong>memory foam mattress</strong> uses heat-reactive foam that contours to your body shape, relieving pressure points and reducing motion transfer — ideal for couples and side sleepers. Both are available in Klawford's mattress range with multiple firmness options.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Which mattress firmness is right for me?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>As a general guide: <strong>Soft</strong> — side sleepers under 10 stone; <strong>Medium</strong> — combination sleepers, average build; <strong>Medium Firm</strong> — back sleepers, most popular option; <strong>Firm</strong> — heavier individuals, back pain sufferers; <strong>Extra Firm</strong> — severe back issues or very heavy individuals. If unsure, our 60-night trial means you can test your choice risk-free at home.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What types of beds do Klawford sell?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Our range includes <strong>upholstered bed frames</strong> (panel, wing-back, and sleigh designs), <strong>divan beds</strong> with optional storage drawers, <strong>ottoman storage beds</strong> with lift-up base, and <strong>luxury bed and mattress sets</strong>. All are available in a variety of premium fabrics and colours including velvet, linen, and faux leather.</p></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-group" data-cat="payment" style="display:none">
          <h2 class="faq-group__title">Finance &amp; Payment</h2>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Do Klawford offer finance or buy now pay later?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Yes — Klawford offers flexible finance and buy now pay later options through trusted UK payment providers. Finance is available at checkout; representative APR and eligibility are displayed before you apply. Spreading the cost means you can invest in a quality bed without paying everything upfront.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What payment methods do you accept?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>We accept all major UK credit and debit cards (Visa, Mastercard, American Express), PayPal, Apple Pay, Google Pay, and finance options. All payments are processed through Shopify's secure, PCI-DSS compliant payment infrastructure — we never store your card details.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">Can I cancel or amend my order?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Orders can be amended or cancelled within <strong>24 hours</strong> of being placed. Because our beds and mattresses are built to order, production begins quickly and cancellation after this window may not be possible. Please email <strong>sales@clickclickstore.co.uk</strong> immediately if you need to make changes.</p></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-group" data-cat="warranty" style="display:none">
          <h2 class="faq-group__title">Warranty &amp; Guarantees</h2>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">What warranty do Klawford beds and mattresses come with?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>All Klawford beds and mattresses are backed by a manufacturer's guarantee covering structural faults and manufacturing defects. The guarantee period varies by product and is listed on each individual product page. Our mattresses also carry our 60-night sleep trial on top of the standard guarantee.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">My Klawford bed arrived damaged — what do I do?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Please note any damage on the delivery paperwork before signing, photograph the issue clearly, and contact us at <strong>sales@clickclickstore.co.uk</strong> within <strong>48 hours</strong> of delivery. We will assess the photographs and arrange a repair, replacement, or refund as quickly as possible — at no cost to you.</p></div></div>
          <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">How do I make a warranty claim?</button><div class="faq-a"><p>Email <strong>sales@clickclickstore.co.uk</strong> with your order number, a description of the issue, and clear photographs of the fault. Our team will respond within 2 working days with a resolution. Please do not attempt to repair the item yourself as this may void the warranty.</p></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-cta">
        <h2 class="info-cta__title">Didn't Find Your Answer?</h2>
        <p class="info-cta__text">Our UK team is available Monday–Friday and happy to help with any question about our beds, mattresses, or ordering process.</p>
        <a href="mailto:sales@clickclickstore.co.uk" class="btn btn--primary">Email Our Team</a>
      </div>
    </div>
